						               													<description>&amp;quot;All the excitement and drama of the Presidential Campaign is captured in this unique new game for the 80's.  Politrix combines the skill and strategy of Presidential Politics with humor &amp;amp; fun!!  Race against opposition as you raise funds, buy votes, and form party tickets on the way to becoming President of the United States.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic roll-and-move with three circular tracks: fundraising, campaigning, and the election.  The &amp;quot;unique&amp;quot; aspect of the game is that when players move into the middle (campaigning) track they must declare a political party (Democan or Republicrat) and only one player of each party may advance to the inner (election) as that party's nominee.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game comes with: a board, 6 plastic tokens, two-page rules, 2 six-sided dice, scorepad, two sets of ballots (33 Democan &amp;amp; 33 Republicrat, 6 @ 50 votes &amp;amp; 27 @ 100 votes each), two event decks (25 &amp;quot;Campaign Strategy&amp;quot; cards and 40 &amp;quot;Between the Headlines&amp;quot; cards), paper money, and a &amp;quot;33rpm recording vital to your campaign&amp;quot; with strategy hints.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
